compounded by the character's constant chest puffing attitude towards the center's staff and doctors and his constant proclamations that he doesn't need to do it their way. The lack of believability also makes it tough to suspend disbelief (even though it is fiction).Overall: With all the hype surrounding and even Oprah getting behind it I was expecting something solid. What I got was something so so. If this genre interests you give "Futureproof: A Novel (P.S.)" a try.22 comments|
