There was a problem loading comments right now. Please try again later.3.0 out of 5 starsWell written, though contrivedByEmily Greitzeron September 5, 2013Format: Paperback|Verified PurchaseI have no real qualms with this book other than the deception of calling it a memoir. Part of the appeal of reading a memoir is trusting that the author is being honest and forthcoming with his account. I knew when I began reading this book that it was exaggerated but while I was reading I found myself unable to believe most of it had even happened. It just smacked of fiction. It seemed unrealistic in parts, and I felt the misuse of the label "memoir" was highly ironic considering how much Frey cites honesty/accountability as being crucial parts of healing from addiction in the book. The eclectic and chaotic writing style was compelling, and I felt easy to read but if you're looking for an accurate, believable memoir of addiction I wouldn't read this book.0Comment|
